```markdown
# ApplyIQ — AI-Powered Personal Job Portal

> Stop sending the same resume to every job. ApplyIQ tailors your resume for every single application using AI — injecting the right keywords, optimizing for ATS, and generating a custom cover letter in seconds.

---

## What It Does

ApplyIQ is a personal job search command center built for serious job seekers. Instead of manually rewriting your resume for every job, ApplyIQ does it automatically — analyzing each job description, extracting the exact keywords recruiters and ATS systems look for, and rewriting your resume to match.

### Core Features

- **Live Job Search** — Searches across LinkedIn, Indeed, Glassdoor, ZipRecruiter, and Google Jobs in real time via JSearch API
- **Paste Any Job URL** — Found a job on any website? Paste the URL and ApplyIQ scrapes the job description automatically
- **AI Resume Tailoring** — Claude AI rewrites your resume for each job following real-world ATS rules: keyword injection, proper formatting, relevant experience reordering, quantified achievements
- **Side-by-Side Review** — See your original resume vs the tailored version side by side. Edit inline before downloading
- **ATS Score** — Get an ATS score and keyword match percentage for every tailored resume before you apply
- **Cover Letter Generator** — Personalized cover letter for each job, written to match the company and role specifically
- **Pre-filled Application Answers** — AI generates answers to common application questions (why this company, relevant experience, salary expectations, work authorization)
- **Download as PDF or Word** — Download your tailored resume in the format the employer needs
- **Application Tracker** — Every application auto-tracked in a Kanban board (Applied → Phone → Interview → Offer)
- **Notes per application** — Add interview notes, contacts, and follow-up reminders

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React 18 + Vite |
| Styling | Vanilla CSS with CSS variables |
| AI Engine | Anthropic Claude API (claude-sonnet) |
| Job Search | JSearch API via RapidAPI |
| PDF Parsing | pdfjs-dist (browser-side) |
| PDF Export | pdf-lib |
| Word Export | docx.js |
| File Downloads | file-saver |
| URL Scraping | Vercel Serverless Functions |
| Storage | localStorage (no database needed) |
| Hosting | Vercel |

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+
- Anthropic API key — [console.anthropic.com](https://console.anthropic.com)
- RapidAPI key (JSearch) — [rapidapi.com](https://rapidapi.com) → search JSearch

### Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Slakkimsetty/ApplyIQ.git
cd ApplyIQ
npm install
```

### Environment Setup

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `.env`:
```
VITE_ANTHROPIC_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here
VITE_RAPIDAPI_KEY=your-rapidapi-key-here
```

### Run Locally

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

---

## How To Use

### First time setup
1. Go to **Profile & Resume** → Upload your PDF resume
2. Fill in your name, title, skills, work authorization → Save

### Finding and applying to jobs
1. Go to **Find Jobs** → Search by title or leave blank to find all matching roles
2. Or paste any job URL directly to scrape it
3. Click **Apply with AI** on any job
4. AI generates your tailored resume, cover letter, and application answers
5. Review the side-by-side comparison — edit anything inline
6. Check your **ATS score** and **keyword match %**
7. Download as PDF or Word
8. Open the application, upload your tailored resume, paste the cover letter
9. Application is automatically tracked in your dashboard

---

## Deployment

Deploy to Vercel for access from any device:

```bash
npm install -g vercel
vercel
```

Add environment variables in Vercel dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables:
- `VITE_ANTHROPIC_KEY`
- `VITE_RAPIDAPI_KEY`

